The `countWordInLine()` function takes a line and a word as input and returns the number of times the word appears in the line. It converts both the line and the word to lowercase using `std::transform()` and `::tolower` before performing the search. This ensures that the search is case insensitive. The function then uses a `while` loop with `std::string::find()` to find all occurrences of the word in the line.

